The article discusses a meeting that President Obama had on energy efficiency and job creation. He visited a Home Depot in Virginia to highlight the importance of providing incentives for consumers to retrofit their homes for energy efficiency. The President met with representatives from the labor, small business, and manufacturing communities to discuss the shift to a more energy efficient economy. After the event, he had lunch with business leaders from different parts of the supply chain to discuss creating jobs through incentivizing home energy efficiency upgrades. The Vice President also sent a memo to the President on the positive impact of the energy components of the Recovery Act, which represents the largest single investment in clean energy in American history. The memo details the progress in renewable energy, vehicles of the future, smart grid, energy efficiency, carbon capture, and science and innovation.